 symbiotic geopolitical and economic relationships between the US state and media firms that drive the production of imperial culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCultural industries--United States. 70(DE-588)104358448X0(DE-627)77069702X0(DE-576)395123798aPublic Diplomacy2gnd 70(DE-588)4000911-70(DE-627)1063994030(DE-576)208840206aAkkulturation2gnd 70(DE-588)4003846-40(DE-627)10438896X0(DE-576)208852972aAußenpolitik2gnd 70(DE-588)4026486-50(DE-627)1062881800(DE-576)208966552aIdeologie2gnd 70(DE-588)4069027-10(DE-627)1061044700(DE-576)209175362aAuswärtige Kulturpolitik2gnd 70(DE-588)4074660-40(DE-627)1060887340(DE-576)209194871aMedienpolitik2gnd 70(DE-588)4116489-10(DE-627)1043252240(DE-576)209502010aSicherheitspolitik2gnd 70(DE-588)4129410-50(DE-627)1057100830(DE-576)209610298aMedienwirtschaft2gnd 70(DE-588)4156741-90(DE-627)1046090010(DE-576)209829168aGeopolitik2gnd 70(DE-588)4161990-00(DE-627)1054657470(DE-576)209870117aInteresse2gnd 70(DE-588)4209283-80(DE-627)1043532010(DE-576)210191112aEinflussgröße2gnd 70(DE-588)4211565-60(DE-627)1050875210(DE-576)21020446XaKulturübertragung2gnd 70(DE-588)4412411-90(DE-627)2119781750(DE-576)212180290aInformationswirtschaft2gnd 70(DE-588)4444998-70(DE-627)2253146140(DE-576)212508466aKulturindustrie2gnd 70(DE-588)4445050-30(DE-627)2253150840(DE-576)212508717aKulturimperialismus2gnd 70(DE-588)4461851-70(DE-627)2307597180(DE-576)212679430aAufgabenträger2gnd 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Cultural Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311127380808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2016z978311127630408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Colum